                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14098782" author="mantonov" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2014 17:24:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;notifications not being triggered&quot; - you mean, region is left in &apos;opened&quot; state until next RS &apos;s ephemeral znodes expires, and when master notices that, is marks all regions hosted by that RS as &quot;closed&quot;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14098814" author="jxiang" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2014 17:47:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not that. It&apos;s about the notification for those AssignmentListeners. For, AM has its own regionOffline method, in which it calls sendRegionClosedNotification(). Sometimes, RegionStates#regionOffline is called directly so the notification call is not invoked.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14098981" author="octo47" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2014 19:34:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;RegionStates can have it&apos;s own set of listeners (but with care, due of locking in RegionsStates, suppose here threadpool can be used).&lt;br/&gt;
And AM, in turn, can register for changes in RegionStates and invoke it&apos;s own listeners.&lt;br/&gt;
Looks a bit complicated, but RS listeners can be triggered on any state changes, not only for open/close.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you think about such design?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
